Step 1: Identify the quick assets. These are the liquid items that do not include inventory. They are:
 • Cash on Hand: 6,057,264.53
 • Bank Deposits: 1,020,005.47
 • Interest Receivable: 14,887.89
 • Accounts Receivable: 14,921,566.06

Step 2: Sum the quick assets.
 Sum = 6,057,264.53 + 1,020,005.47 + 14,887.89 + 14,921,566.06
   = 22,013,723.95

Step 3: Identify the total current liabilities.
 Total Current Liabilities = 8,028,630.43

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio.
 Quick Ratio = (Total Quick Assets) / (Total Current Liabilities)
   = 22,013,723.95 / 8,028,630.43
   ≈ 2.74

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {'Quick Ratio': '2.74'}}
